    com.cisco.pxgrid.Configuration.setGroup(String)
    this is replaced with setGroups to support multiple groups use #setGroups() instead (Optional) Sets the access group that the user wants to be part of. By default, the user is put into “Basic” group which is the least access level group. Please note that this parameter just specifies the node’s intent to be part of a particular group at the time of account creation. The system administrator can change it at any time. Currently supported groups are “Basic”, “Session” and “EPS”.
